The article, written by Vice President Michael R. Pence, commemorates the 50th anniversary of the Apollo 11 moon landing and discusses the importance of American leadership in space. Pence highlights the challenges faced by the United States in meeting President Kennedy's call to put a man on the moon, but emphasizes the courage and determination of the Apollo 11 crew and NASA in achieving this historic feat. He argues that unity was the true legacy of Apollo 11 and calls for a renewal of American commitment to space exploration. Pence mentions President Trump's efforts to revitalize the National Space Council and involve American companies in the space industry. He announces that the United States plans to establish a base at the moon's South Pole and eventually set foot on Mars. Pence concludes by expressing confidence in American leadership in space under President Trump's administration.